6. What is SKU and why is it used?
→ SKU (Stock Keeping Unit) is a unique identifier for each product used to track inventory efficiently.


7. What is the difference between batch tracking and serial tracking?

Batch tracking: Tracks groups of items with same batch ID (e.g., medicines).

Serial tracking: Tracks individual items with unique serial numbers (e.g., electronics).



8. What is FIFO and LIFO in inventory?

FIFO (First In First Out): First purchased items are sold first.

LIFO (Last In First Out): Last purchased items are sold first.
